    "description": "Torasemide is a loop diuretic (water pill) used to reduce fluid retention (edema) associated with conditions such as heart failure, liver cirrhosis, and kidney disorders. It works by blocking the reabsorption of sodium and chloride in the kidneys, which leads to increased urine production and a subsequent decrease in fluid accumulation in the body. Torasemide is often prescribed in combination with other medications to manage hypertension and to alleviate symptoms of congestive heart failure.",
    
    "uses": "Torasemide is primarily used for the management of edema in patients with conditions like heart failure, liver cirrhosis, and renal disease. It is also effective in treating hypertension, either alone or as an adjunct to other antihypertensive agents. Additionally, it may be utilized in cases where other diuretics are ineffective or unsuitable, making it a versatile option in clinical practice.\n\nMoreover, torasemide can be beneficial in managing specific complications of heart or kidney diseases by helping to maintain fluid balance, thereby improving patients' overall quality of life and potentially reducing hospitalizations due to fluid overload.",
    
    "side effects": [
